<div class="section" id="gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp">
  <div class="section" id="gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky">
    <h2>Sticky Topics</h2>
    <p>
      A <em class="wordasword">sticky</em> topic is shown before all the
      other topics in the <cite class="tab">Topic</cite> tab on the
      group page.
      An administrator can
      <a href="#gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky-add">add a
      topic to the sticky topics,</a>
      and
      <a href="#gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky-remove">remove
      a topics from the sticky topics.</a>
    </p>
    <div class="section"
         id="gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky-add">
      <h3>Add a Topic to the Sticky Topics</h3>
      <p>
        To add a topic to the list of sticky topics for the group carry
        out the following tasks.
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Vist the topic.</li>
        <li>Select the <samp class="checkbox">Sicky</samp> checkbox.
        The topic will be added to the sicky topics.</li>
      </ol>
    </div><!--gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky-add-->
    <div class="section"
         id="gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky-remove">
      <h3>Remove a Topic to the Sticky Topics</h3>
      <p>
        To remove a topic from the list of sticky topics for the group
        carry out the following tasks.
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Vist the topic.</li>
        <li>Deselect the <samp class="checkbox">Sicky</samp> checkbox.
        The topic will be removed from the sicky topics.</li>
      </ol>
    </div><!--gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky-remove-->
  </div><!--gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-sticky-->
</div><!--gs-group-messages-topic-adminhelp-->
